<div id="review_1155564025" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1155564025" />
    <a title="Anne OK" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/285610-anne-ok"><img alt="Anne OK" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1505981069p2/285610.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1155564025?book_show_action=true">Jan 04, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anne OK" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anne OK" href="/user/show/285610-anne-ok">Anne OK</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/285610-anne-ok?shelf=2015-reads">2015-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1155564025" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9644471812107233309">This book contains one of those controversial storylines drawn straight from today’s headlines. From the blurb, readers will immediately know that they are on a path filled with sadness and pain as Ciera and Topher tell their story. But there’s so much more, too. I was moved to tears and crushed by its heartbreaking message. I was also touched by the sweet laughter and tender moments that were shared by this young couple amid the serious issues covered. This is also the kind of story that you ge</span>
  <span id="freeText9644471812107233309" style="display:none">This book contains one of those controversial storylines drawn straight from today’s headlines. From the blurb, readers will immediately know that they are on a path filled with sadness and pain as Ciera and Topher tell their story. But there’s so much more, too. I was moved to tears and crushed by its heartbreaking message. I was also touched by the sweet laughter and tender moments that were shared by this young couple amid the serious issues covered. This is also the kind of story that you get lost in and is hard to forget. It reminds us of all the good that can come from a little forgiveness and kindness towards one another. One act of kindness can go a long way in brightening another’s day. <br /><br />My biggest complaint is with where the author chose to end this story. Although I find no mention of it, I am hopeful that Topher will get a conclusion to his story in a future book. I want to know that he has moved on from the loss and sadness. Readers need to see the new and improved Topher find his happily-ever-after. As it stands, there are some unanswered questions that leave Topher hanging from the cliff. This reader is definitely begging for more.<br /><br />The author did an admirable job in developing and growing the characters. Opposites that attract discover and nurture a friendship that turns an ugly situation into something special and rewarding. The hurt and pain, along with the growing relationship between Topher and Ciera, is written in a realistic and believable manner. <br /><br />Notice was taken of some minor editing problems throughout the book that could have used the eye of a good proofreader. They won’t interfere with the rewards of the story itself, but irritating when they pop up on the pages.<br /><br />Overall, a solid and memorable reading experience. I will definitely continue with this series.<br /><br /><br /><i>Note: I was gifted a copy from the author in exchange for an unbiased and honest review.</i><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9644471812107233309" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


