    <a title="aNneMarLi - Chatterbooks Book Blog" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30077980-annemarli---chatterbooks-book-blog"><img alt="aNneMarLi - Chatterbooks Book Blog" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1479012572p2/30077980.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1443757804?book_show_action=true">Nov 15, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="aNneMarLi - Chatterbooks Book Blog" class="user" itemprop="url" name="aNneMarLi - Chatterbooks Book Blog" href="/user/show/30077980-annemarli---chatterbooks-book-blog">aNneMarLi - Chatterbooks Book Blog</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30077980-annemarli---chatterbooks-book-blog?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1443757804" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17713967377469703684">Learning to Live is actually my first Kira Adams book, and to say my first, HELL! Definitely it wont be my last. When I was given a copy of this story, I was kinda &quot;Oh the blurb&quot;. Might as well be prepared with Kleenex and a glass of wine or two. <br/><br/>True to this, I needed more than wine or Kleenex for that matter. I wanted more. The story I thought started off easy became gut wrenching and will drain you emotionally. This is not your typical high school romance turned true love then TADA! Happily E</span>
  <span id="freeText17713967377469703684" style="display:none">Learning to Live is actually my first Kira Adams book, and to say my first, HELL! Definitely it wont be my last. When I was given a copy of this story, I was kinda "Oh the blurb". Might as well be prepared with Kleenex and a glass of wine or two. <br /><br />True to this, I needed more than wine or Kleenex for that matter. I wanted more. The story I thought started off easy became gut wrenching and will drain you emotionally. This is not your typical high school romance turned true love then TADA! Happily Ever After. No, it was far from it. This is where you experience an emotional topsy-turvy on two different people from two different worlds whom one taught the other to live while the other to let go. <br /><br />" In one year I felt every emotion imaginable: sadness, hopelessness, happiness, even guilt. In one year I kissed a boy and fell in love. In one year I was able to realize the reason for living. It's love and it's you. Hold on to that. you did that for me. You were selfless."<br /><br />Read the book. Savor every moment of it. Then finally, realize,<br /><br />"Sometimes you have to let go to really live. Sometimes being alive means taking risks."<br /><br />4 HEARTBREAKING STARS!</span>
  <a data-text-id="17713967377469703684" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


