<span id="freeTextContainer1225024348294170155">*Book received in exchange for honest review.*<br/><br/>Topher Carlson is the most popular guy in school, plays football, dating the high school cheer squad captain, comes from money, and lavishes in sexy cars. Sophia, the cheer head, is little miss perfect, feeling superior above all others, she bullies. She bullies the one girl in school who is different because she doesn&apos;t come from money, can&apos;t afford nice clothes or nice hair. Sophia, Topher, Joe and gang. Formerly known as the A-Team, make her life </span>
  <span id="freeText1225024348294170155" style="display:none">*Book received in exchange for honest review.*<br /><br />Topher Carlson is the most popular guy in school, plays football, dating the high school cheer squad captain, comes from money, and lavishes in sexy cars. Sophia, the cheer head, is little miss perfect, feeling superior above all others, she bullies. She bullies the one girl in school who is different because she doesn't come from money, can't afford nice clothes or nice hair. Sophia, Topher, Joe and gang. Formerly known as the A-Team, make her life a living hell for six years straight. Poor Ciera Nelson, she has just one friend, Mack. She never looks anyone in the eye and is a straight A student. After one horrid incident involving the A-Team in the school bathrooms, she is befriended by one of them, Madlynne. She takes Ciera under her wing and turns her into someone beautiful and gives her more confidence then she has ever had. Topher can't take his eyes off her, or get her out his mind. One thing leads to another....But Ciera is hiding a massive secrets from her few friends and peers, how will she tell the people she cares about? How will they react?<br /><br />Damn it to hell and back. This book had me sobbing on multiple occasions, full blown wailing at the end. This book is beautifully written and the storyline is portrayed with dignity and respect. It's a love story with an ending that I'm not used to. But my goodness, this has my heart, hook, line and sinker. I would like to see where Topher's life leads and how he copes.<br /><br />This is a YA novel, with slight sexual content.<br /><br /></span>
