<div id="review_1322648694" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1322648694" />
    <a title="Joan Clark" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/42507591-joan-clark"><img alt="Joan Clark" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1429995932p2/42507591.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1322648694?book_show_action=true">Jul 01, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joan Clark" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joan Clark" href="/user/show/42507591-joan-clark">Joan Clark</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1322648694" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6422299072848759414">4.5 Stars. This is not your average romance or HEA. If that is something you need than this book isn&apos;t for you. This book had me experiencing such a range of emotions that I don&apos;t know if I could even identify them all. Ciera begins the story as a bullied young woman that I pitied. The farther the plot progressed the more I realized Ciera was one of the strongest characters I have read. Topher, well let&apos;s just say I hated him in the beginning. In fact I&apos;m not sure hate is a strong enough word. I</span>
  <span id="freeText6422299072848759414" style="display:none">4.5 Stars. This is not your average romance or HEA. If that is something you need than this book isn't for you. This book had me experiencing such a range of emotions that I don't know if I could even identify them all. Ciera begins the story as a bullied young woman that I pitied. The farther the plot progressed the more I realized Ciera was one of the strongest characters I have read. Topher, well let's just say I hated him in the beginning. In fact I'm not sure hate is a strong enough word. I truly didn't see redemption being in my eyes for him. Boy was I wrong. Ms. Adams has weaved a tale that grabbed my heart and took me right along for the ride. The flow, character development, and plot were smooth, captivating, and intriguing. If you enjoy an emotional explosion that takes control of your tear ducts than I highly recommend this book for you. It is one I will not soon forget.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6422299072848759414" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1322648694">
  <td colspan="2">
