<div id="review_1151150399" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1151150399" />
    <a title="Lou" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18531895-lou"><img alt="Lou" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1532878748p2/18531895.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1151150399?book_show_action=true">Jan 02, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lou" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lou" href="/user/show/18531895-lou">Lou</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1151150399" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer177756382281123001">Oh... My... Word!!! I think my heart has been shredded... <br/><br/>My full review to follow, but in the meantime; Read this book!!!<br/><br/>14/01/15 Full Review:<br/><br/>Oh My Days... Where do I start? This book is AMAZING!! I LOVE IT SO MUCH!! (OK, enough shouting)!!<br/><br/>Learning To Live (LTL), has introduced me to Ciera and Topher. These two attend the same school, but are in completely different situations.<br/><br/>Ciera; spends here days head down; not making eye contact with anyone in the hopes of blending in or becoming invisible</span>
  <span id="freeText177756382281123001" style="display:none">Oh... My... Word!!! I think my heart has been shredded... <br /><br />My full review to follow, but in the meantime; Read this book!!!<br /><br />14/01/15 Full Review:<br /><br />Oh My Days... Where do I start? This book is AMAZING!! I LOVE IT SO MUCH!! (OK, enough shouting)!!<br /><br />Learning To Live (LTL), has introduced me to Ciera and Topher. These two attend the same school, but are in completely different situations.<br /><br />Ciera; spends here days head down; not making eye contact with anyone in the hopes of blending in or becoming invisible. Why? because there are certain people at school who go out of their way to make her life pretty shit, they make fun of her and try to find ways to humiliate her. After receiving some devastating news can Ciera learn to live and not hide in the shadows?<br /><br />Topher; is Mr Popular! He's part of the popular group, plays on the football team, dates a cheerleader. Most guys want to be him and most girls want to be his. He's also a part of the group that laugh at Ciera. But when his dad brings someone home to meet Topher, suddenly Topher's world threatens to come crashing down. Can Topher learn that being popular isn't the be all and end all?<br /><br />Ciera had my heart from the very start! She's realistic and down to Earth. She's studying at school as well as working to help her mother raise her two siblings, and then she looks after her siblings so her mum can work. Ciera's character right from the start had heaps of potential and as the story in LTL developed so did Ciera, her character goes from strength to strength. Even when faced with something very real and scary; Ciera still continued to grow and refused to give up.<br /><br />Topher on the other hand! At the start my first impression of him is what a complete and utter Dick!!! I'll admit that maybe I was a little harsh. As I continued to read LTL Topher grew on me, and I couldn't help but like him too. Topher had a lot to learn and with some help he does begin to realize that there are bigger things in the world. I couldn't stop the way my heart broke for him. Topher has certainly earned his place in my heart and I'd love to read more about him.<br /><br />Kira has written another amazing story, that's packed full of emotion. LTL has made me smile and laugh, its made me feel hurt and anger, its touched my heart (well torn it out and shredded it into tiny little pieces) and made me cry too (when I say cry I mean ugly cry). Kira has managed to suck me into the very heart of this beautiful story so that when I finished reading I felt as though I was leaving behind friends not just characters.<br /><br />I have thoroughly enjoyed every last page of LTL. So what are you waiting for go grab yourself a box of tissues and a copy of Learning To Live!<br /><br />Learning To Live earns a whopping 5* from me, and I cannot wait to get my teeth into another of Kira's books!</span>
  <a data-text-id="177756382281123001" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


