<div id="review_1152961746" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1152961746" />
    <a title="Heather" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4971603-heather"><img alt="Heather" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1152961746?book_show_action=true">Jan 02, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heather" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heather" href="/user/show/4971603-heather">Heather</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1152961746" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5099328055809836907">I was given an ARC (advanced release copy) from the author in exchange for an honest review.<br/><br/>Synopsis:<br/><br/>Ciera Nelson wants what any other outcast wants, invisibility. If she can just make it through the rest of her year with minor incidents and a head held low she will be able to put the hell hole they call school in her rearview. Unfortunately, life has different plans for her. <br/><br/>Topher Carlson is one of the biggest jocks on campus. All the guys want to be him, all the girls want to claim him. When </span>
  <span id="freeText5099328055809836907" style="display:none">I was given an ARC (advanced release copy) from the author in exchange for an honest review.<br /><br />Synopsis:<br /><br />Ciera Nelson wants what any other outcast wants, invisibility. If she can just make it through the rest of her year with minor incidents and a head held low she will be able to put the hell hole they call school in her rearview. Unfortunately, life has different plans for her. <br /><br />Topher Carlson is one of the biggest jocks on campus. All the guys want to be him, all the girls want to claim him. When secrets are uncovered, Topher’s life spins wildly out of control.<br /><br />They are far from friends when the school year begins, but each will impact the other’s life in ways they never dreamed possible. Can Ciera help Topher realize that popularity and status mean nothing in the real world? Can Topher help Ciera learn the true meaning of living?<br /><br /><br />My review:<br />“I love how romance authors can make you feel every emotion in their books that you feel invested in the characters. By the end of the story, you feel as if you know them on some kind of personal level, and you mourn the loss of them when it’s over.” Ciera, Learning to Live<br /><br />The above quote sums up how I felt about this book. Ms. Adams’ book will make you have every emotion possible. Anger, hurt, and pain for Ciera when she is bullied by her peers to happiness, joy, love, and eventually pain with her nemesis turned lover, Topher.<br /><br />"Learning to Live" is a well written, easy to read book that left me in tears. Ciera and Topher are great characters and the storyline was easy to follow. This book flowed very well with no big gaps in the story. I really felt a connection to Ciera and Topher and wish their story would have ended differently.<br /><br />I finished the book in a few hours. I couldn’t put it down and wanted to see how it all played out and though I wished it would have ended differently, I don’t see a way that it could have. <br /><br />This book isn’t a light hearted read as there is some very serious topics in it, but I wouldn’t say it was a super “ugly cry” book. I did shed some tears and it definitely made me think of some things that I hadn’t ever thought of before.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5099328055809836907" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


