<div id="review_1232336329" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1232336329" />
    <a title="Rhiannon St. Clair" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3275485-rhiannon-st-clair"><img alt="Rhiannon St. Clair" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1556670027p2/3275485.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1232336329?book_show_action=true">Mar 20, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rhiannon St. Clair" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rhiannon St. Clair" href="/user/show/3275485-rhiannon-st-clair">Rhiannon St. Clair</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3275485-rhiannon-st-clair?shelf=read-in-2015">read-in-2015</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1232336329" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12799167692784625685">***I received an eBook ARC from the author in exchange for an honest review***<br/><br/>This book is the perfect start to what I am guessing will be an amazing series.<br/><br/>Topher and Ciara are polar opposites. He’s popular, she’s not. He’s rich, she’s poor. He’s forgotten how to live and she’s trying to learn how to do so. When they come together, it takes everyone around them by surprise and sets their worlds on fire.<br/><br/>Kira already proved to me that she could write an amazing action book when I read Into the Da</span>
  <span id="freeText12799167692784625685" style="display:none">***I received an eBook ARC from the author in exchange for an honest review***<br /><br />This book is the perfect start to what I am guessing will be an amazing series.<br /><br />Topher and Ciara are polar opposites. He’s popular, she’s not. He’s rich, she’s poor. He’s forgotten how to live and she’s trying to learn how to do so. When they come together, it takes everyone around them by surprise and sets their worlds on fire.<br /><br />Kira already proved to me that she could write an amazing action book when I read Into the Darkness. Learning to Live has showed me even more of her immense talent, this time proving that she can also write young adult angst and romance as well.<br /><br />I found myself appreciating Ciara the most in this book. I think a lot of the reason I did was because I’d had some of the same experiences as her, and therefore I felt like she was more relatable for me than the other characters were. I appreciated the fact that Kira created a character that was strong, even in the face of bad news and heartache. She knew what she wanted and she stood by the choices she made for herself. She commanded respect, and her transformation throughout the book was beautiful to watch.<br /><br />Topher’s transformation was amazing. Kira wrote about him in a way that was realistic, nothing about his changes felt too rushed to me, and through her writing I could really see and feel the conviction in his words and actions.<br /><br />The whole time I was reading this I couldn’t help but think of A Walk to Remember. This book had a very similar feel to that one. I loved how Kira was able to take something tragic and spin it around so that it ended up being miraculous, special, and positive in many ways.<br /><br />I already went out and got the rest of the Infinite Love Series. I would definitely recommend checking this story out. It’s a short read, it’s well-written, it flows smoothly, and it’s written in a way that made it hard for me to put down because I craved more of the characters.<br /><br />5 stars to this book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="12799167692784625685" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


